    <p id="p_kwv_bgk_54b">A schema annotation is a documentation snippet associated with the definition of an element
      or attribute in a schema. If such a schema is associated with an XML document, the annotations
      are displayed in:<ul id="ul_lwv_bgk_54b">
        <li id="li_mwv_bgk_54b">The <xref keyref="glossentry_content-completion-assistant"><term>Content Completion
              Assistant</term></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_nwv_bgk_54b">A small tooltip window shown when the mouse hovers over an element or attribute.<ph
            product="editor author developer"> The tooltip window can be invoked at any time by
            using the <uicontrol><shortcut>F2</shortcut></uicontrol> shortcut.</ph></li>
      </ul></p>
